# Conference Paper (Condensed)

**Purpose:** Write and present at academic conferences.

**Links to:** paper-writing, journal-q1-polish, publication-strategy, technical-english-cs, defense-prep

---

## Conference vs Journal

| Aspect | Conference | Journal |
|--------|-----------|---------|
| Length | 4-6 pages | 8-12 pages |
| Review | 2-3 months | 3-12 months |
| Novelty | High | Moderate |
| Experiments | Key results | Comprehensive |

## Paper Structure (4-6 pages)

1. Introduction (0.5-1p): problem + gap + contributions
2. Related Work (0.5-1p): 2-3 paragraphs
3. Method (1.5-2p): formulation + algorithm + complexity
4. Experiments (1-1.5p): setup + main results + ablation
5. Conclusion (0.25p): summary + future work

## Poster Design (A0)

```
┌──────────┬──────────┬──────────┐
│ Intro    │ Method   │ Related  │
├──────────┼──────────┼──────────┤
│ Results  │ Results  │ Conclusion│
└──────────┴──────────┴──────────┘
```

## Oral Presentation (15 min)

| Section | Time | Slides |
|---------|------|--------|
| Intro | 2 min | 2-3 |
| Related Work | 1 min | 1 |
| Method | 5 min | 3-4 |
| Experiments | 4 min | 2-3 |
| Conclusion | 1 min | 1 |

## Camera-Ready Checklist

- [ ] Address all reviewer comments
- [ ] Figure quality 300 DPI
- [ ] Page limits respected
- [ ] Copyright form signed
- [ ] Conference registration done

## Conference Formats

- NeurIPS/ICML: 4p + unlimited appendix, double-blind
- CVPR/ICCV: 8p, IEEE template
- ACL/EMNLP: 8p long / 4p short
- IEEE: 4-6p, IEEE double-column
